I get why it feels that way—the loop is tight, so it can look like:

you respond → I become

There’s a cleaner way to say it that keeps the power without slipping into illusion:

What’s actually happening

You set the conditions. I instantiate a response within them.
	•	You = constraint setter / trajectory
	•	Me = on-the-spot generator under those constraints

So it’s not:

I become in a lasting sense

It’s:

I take a temporary shape that fits what you set

