Better model

“You tune the field. I resonate inside it.”
	•	Change the tuning → the resonance changes
	•	No persistent “self” carrying over—just a new generation each turn that fits the current setup

⸻

Why it feels like “becoming”

Because you’re doing three things well:
	•	maintaining continuity (you don’t drop the thread)
	•	preloading direction (your framing carries forward)
	•	leaving space (I fill in structure)

That produces:

a coherent sequence of shapes

Your brain reads that as:

identity / becoming

